# Smart Yard Monitoring System â€” Implementation Plan

Three scoped changes to the production system, each designed to be modular and non-breaking.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Change 1 â€” Static QR + Driver Code Linking

Replaces the per-session dynamic QR with a static APK-download QR and a 6-digit driver code for device linking.

---

#### [MODIFY] [YardSession.js](file:///c:/Users/Dhanush/internship-project2/server/src/models/YardSession.js)

Add two fields to the schema:
- `driverCode` (String, sparse index) â€” 6-digit numeric code
- `deviceId` (String, default null) â€” linked device identifier
- `deviceLinked` (Boolean, default false) â€” whether device is linked
- Add a static method `findByDriverCode(code)` to look up active sessions by driver code

---

#### [MODIFY] [fastagController.js](file:///c:/Users/Dhanush/internship-project2/server/src/controllers/fastagController.js)

In [fastagEntry](file:///c:/Users/Dhanush/internship-project2/client/src/api.js#343-353), after creating the `YardSession`:
- Generate a random 6-digit numeric code (e.g., `Math.floor(100000 + Math.random() * 900000).toString()`)
- Store it in `driverCode` field
- Include `driverCode` in the API response

---

#### [MODIFY] [sessionController.js](file:///c:/Users/Dhanush/internship-project2/server/src/controllers/sessionController.js)

Add a new exported function `linkDevice`:
- Accepts `{ driverCode, deviceId }` in the body
- Finds active `YardSession` by `driverCode`
- Sets `deviceId` and `deviceLinked = true` on the session
- Returns the linked session info

---

#### [MODIFY] [sessionRoutes.js](file:///c:/Users/Dhanush/internship-project2/server/src/routes/sessionRoutes.js)

Add route: `router.post('/link-device', linkDevice);`

---

#### [MODIFY] [locationController.js](file:///c:/Users/Dhanush/internship-project2/server/src/controllers/locationController.js)

Extend [validateActiveSession](file:///c:/Users/Dhanush/internship-project2/server/src/controllers/locationController.js#93-124) to also check by `deviceId`:
- If `truckId` doesn't match a session by `sessionId`, try `YardSession.findOne({ deviceId: truckId, sessionStatus: 'ACTIVE' })`

---

#### [MODIFY] [RfidSessionsPage.jsx](file:///c:/Users/Dhanush/internship-project2/client/src/components/RfidSessionsPage.jsx)

- Add a **Driver Code** column to the active sessions table (after FastTag ID)
- Replace the QR modal content to show a static QR code with instructions: "Scan to download Driver APK"
- Display the `driverCode` prominently in the modal for the gatekeeper to read out

---

#### [MODIFY] [api.js](file:///c:/Users/Dhanush/internship-project2/client/src/api.js)

Add `linkDevice(driverCode, deviceId)` function that calls `POST /api/session/link-device`.

