### Change 3 â€” Tamper Alerts Integration

Ensures tamper events (DEVICE_REMOVED, BLE_DISCONNECTED, MAGNETIC_DEVICE_REMOVED, DEVICE_OFFLINE) are logged to EventLog and visible in the dashboard.

---

#### [MODIFY] [alertsController.js](file:///c:/Users/Dhanush/internship-project2/server/src/controllers/alertsController.js)

Add tamper event types to `alertEventTypes` array in [getDashboardAlerts](file:///c:/Users/Dhanush/internship-project2/client/src/api.js#181-188):
```js
const alertEventTypes = [
    'OUT_OF_YARD', 'ZONE_ANOMALY', 'SPEED_VIOLATION', 'GEOFENCE_VIOLATION',
    'DEVICE_REMOVED', 'BLE_DISCONNECTED', 'MAGNETIC_DEVICE_REMOVED', 'DEVICE_OFFLINE'
];
```

---

#### [NEW] Export a new `reportTamperEvent` function in [alertsController.js](file:///c:/Users/Dhanush/internship-project2/server/src/controllers/alertsController.js)

`POST /api/alerts/tamper` endpoint:
- Accepts `{ truckId, sessionId, eventType, location, timestamp }`
- Validates `eventType` is one of the tamper types
- Creates an `EventLog` entry with severity `high` or `critical`
- Returns success

---

#### [MODIFY] [alertsRoutes.js](file:///c:/Users/Dhanush/internship-project2/server/src/routes/alertsRoutes.js)

Add route: `router.post('/tamper', reportTamperEvent);`

---

#### [MODIFY] [AlertsPanel.jsx](file:///c:/Users/Dhanush/internship-project2/client/src/components/AlertsPanel.jsx)

Add tamper event icons to `ALERT_ICONS`:
```js
DEVICE_REMOVED: 'đź”Ś',
